Data Scientist / Developer		IXIS		Burlington, Vermont Area		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p>IXIS is seeking an energetic individual with experience in digital analytics as well as other types of data to fill the position of Data Engineer for the company. The ideal candidate will be a systematic thinker with a solid foundation in computer science and will also possess the “data IQ” necessary for understanding and working with large and disparate datasets. The core responsibilities for this role include overseeing the execution of digital analytics technical implementations, troubleshooting configurations, and performing and automating data excavation and and reporting. </p><p></p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong> </p><ul><li>Support our data science team by building custom digital analytics implementations and account configurations based on unique data needs and business requirements </li><li>Audit and/or troubleshoot existing digital analytics implementations to ensure data quality </li><li>Work with our data science and development teams to design and implement automated data analysis technologies in support of client deliverables </li><li>Import, normalize, and explore large datasets as a part of data warehousing initiatives </li><li>Collaborate with technical, development, and QA resources<p> </p></li></ul><p><strong>Required Education and Skills:</strong> </p><ul><li>B.A./B.S. in Computer Science; or B.A./B.S. in Statistics/Mathematics with a minor in Computer Science  </li><li>2+ years experience working with JavaScript and HTML 5 for web development </li><li>Intermediate to advanced Excel skills </li><li>Experience working with real-world datasets, including data scraping, record linkage, data cleaning/preparation/management, and descriptive data analysis </li><li>Core critical thinking skills, including good data intuition </li><li>Experience multitasking and prioritizing data initiatives with minimal guidance and instruction at times<p> </p></li></ul><p><strong>Additional Desired Skills:</strong> </p><ul><li>Experience with statistical programming, ideally R </li><li>SQL database experience; additional NoSQL experience (such as MongoDB or Hadoop) ideal </li><li>Development experience in a Linux or Mac environment</li></ul></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p>Founded in 2012, IXIS is rooted in innovative processes for data-driven digital experience and strategic online planning. IXIS works closely with clients to integrate and synchronize traditional and digital marketing initiatives to recalibrate and connect brands across converging media.</p></div>